<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12079b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12079b">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12079b"> 79(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> SP Budik (Victor) / Constantin (Bret) / Ambroise-churl / Uter-Arthur</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Un jour, &agrave; leur requ&ecirc;te, le chef de la p&eacute;ninsule leur avait envoy&eacute; trois mille hommes et trois mille chevaux avec son fr&egrave;re Constantin, pour les d&eacute;livrer des Pictes et des Scots. Ce dernier, ayant donn&eacute; la victoire, avait re&ccedil;u la couronne, et de lui &eacute;taient n&eacute;s trois fils: l&apos;un qui fut assassin&eacute;, &agrave; l&apos;instigation de Guortigern, son ministre; les deux autres, appel&eacute;s Ambroise et Uter, qui cherch&egrave;rent leur salut &agrave; la cour de leur oncle, l&apos;Armoricain Budik ou le Victorieux. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> c&apos;est surtout d&apos;Ambroise et de son fr&egrave;re que s&apos;occupe la tradition occidentale; le premier, qui reb&acirc;tira les &eacute;glises de l&apos;&icirc;le de Bretagne, d&eacute;vast&eacute;es par les adorateurs d&apos;Odin; le second, qui sera p&egrave;re d&apos;Arthur. <br><font color="green">[One day, at their request, the chief of the peninsula had sent them three thousand men and three thousand horses with his brother <mark>Constantin</mark>, to free them from the Picts and the Scots. The latter, having gained victory, had received the crown, and three sons were born to him: one was assassinated, at the instigation of Guortigern, his minister; the other two, who were called <mark>Ambrose and Uter</mark>, sought refuge at the court of their uncle, the Armorican <mark>Budic or <i>the Victorious</i></mark>. [&hellip;]</font> western tradition is especially interested in Ambrose and his brother; the former rebuilt the churches of the isle of Brittany that had been destroyed by the worshippers of Odin; the latter would become the father of Arthur] <small> [TLMM]Th&eacute;odore-Claude Hersart, Vicomte de La Villemarqu&eacute;, <cite a>Myrdhinn, ou l'enchanteur Merlin</cite></a> (1862) 100-3</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
